description:
Love is in the Wild

Science Documentary hosted by Jodie Forrest, published by Arte in 2011 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

&quot;Eat or be eaten&quot; is not the only law in nature. All species, be they predators or preys, are eventually looking for the same thing: a partner to pair and give life... in other words: love! But as among humans, the path to it can be long and tricky. One must go through a succession of well-organized rituals, which are very rich, very subtle and very diverse among species.
Whether funny, unusual, astonishing, violent or tender, animal rituals are always a mirror of the human behavior!
Embark with us on a spectacular journey all around the globe, from the Australian bush to the forests of Europe, to discover the most extraordinary love stories of the world!


1)  One Day in the Forest 
An insight into the animals, flora and fauna found in woodlands and fields as spring approaches

2)  One Day in Australia 
An exploration of the wildlife of Australia. Isolated from the rest of the world for more than 40 million years, the huge continent has one of the planet's oldest landscapes, with an array of flora and fauna found nowhere else on Earth

3)  A Monkeys Life 
Focus on the world of monkeys, and how despite their typical behavioural traits such as grooming, quarreling over everything, and copious amounts of eating and sleeping, there are subtle differences between primate species

4)  One Day in the Savannah 
A discovery of life in the African Savannah. Despite popular images of predators reigning mercilessly and herbivores trying to avoid becoming their prey, the inhabitants also spend a lot of time maintaining social relations

